canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject is a direct cause or primary driver of the object within the context of thermal fatigue phenomena.
Links a damage mechanism or underlying phenomenon to its typical observable manifestation or damage form.
Links a phenomenon or damage event to the physical component or region in which it occurs.
Indicates that the subject condition or mechanism promotes or contributes causally to the occurrence of the object failure mode, without implying strict sufficiency or necessity.
Indicates that the subject condition or process causes, initiates, or worsens the occurrence or severity of the damage or phenomenon represented by the object.
Indicates that the subject process or condition inherently includes the object phenomenon or sub-process as part of its behavior or composition.
